-- Brazauskas, First President of Independent Lithuania, Dies After Illness
-- Milda Seputyte
-- 2010-06-28T06:05:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/brazauskas-first-president-of-independent-lithuania-dies-after-illness.html

          
          
             Former Lithuanian President  Algirdas Mykolas Brazauskas , age 77, died after a long illness, according
to a statement on the presidential Web site.  
 Brazauskas, the nation’s first president after his country
won independence from the Soviet Union in 1990, held office
between 1993 and 1998. He was also the longest-serving
Lithuania’s prime minister since independence and held the post
between 2001 and 2006.  
 Brazauskas’ political career started with the Communist
Party when Lithuania was part of the Soviet Union. As president,
he led Lithuania’s bids to join NATO and the European Union.  
 Brazauskas was the country’s second-most popular politician
in June after current President  Dalia Grybauskaite , according to
an opinion poll conducted in by Vilmorus for Valstybe.  
